<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Female</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">n</emphasis>
= 4): body length 7-8 mm, wing length 8-9 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Female</emphasis>
resembling male in head, thorax and wing. Female terminalia dull brown. Cercus yellowish brown, slightly arched dorsally at apex, slender, 3 times longer than wide at base. Hypogynial valve 3.7 times longer than wide at base; lateral margin with triangular, black marking (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 9. Limonia macrostigma, female 8 cercus and hypogynial valves, lateral view 9 cercus and hypogynial valves, ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures8-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456134" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">8-9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures8-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456134" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" start="Figures 8–9" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Figures 8-9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schummel" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limonia macrostigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostigma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Limonia macrostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
